{
  "texts": [
    "In this paper, we use mainly models derived from the BERT model.",
    "BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) was introduced by Devlin et al. (2019) and developed to state-of-the-art on a large number of NLP tasks.",
    "The BERT model has over 100 million parameters, which are pre-trained on two tasks, Masked Language Modelling (MLM) and Next-Sentence Prediction (NSP).",
    "This pretraining is performed on a large corpus of text data.",
    "The language mix of this text corpus determines the language(s) understood by the model."
  ]
}